text: Kazadayevka () is a rural locality (a village) in Kazadayevsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 51 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 9 km from Sterlitamak, 4 km from Novoye Baryatino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Kazadayevka
